H0.text: Amniotic fluid is the type of fluid that cushions the fetus and helps protect it from injury.

H1.text: Plasmid is the type of fluid that cushions the fetus and helps protect it from injury.

H2.text: Epithelial is the type of fluid that cushions the fetus and helps protect it from injury.

H3.text: Aqueous fluid cushions the fetus and helps protect it from injury.

A4.text: Amniotic fluid protects the developing fetus by cushioning against blows to the mother's abdomen, allowing for easier fetal movement, and promoting muscular/skeletal development.

A5.text: Amniotic fluid is the protective liquid contained by the amniotic sac of a gravid amniote. This fluid serves as a cushion for the growing fetus
